26 21-8-608. Use of state or local funds to contract with lobbyist
27 prohibited.
28 (a) A governmental body shall not use state or local funds to enter
29 into a contract with a lobbyist for the purpose of lobbying on behalf of the
30 governmental body.
31 (b) The prohibition under subsection (a) of this section includes
32 without limitation the use of state or local funds by a governmental body to
33 pay membership dues to an organization that engages in lobbying on behalf of
34 the governmental body or similar governmental bodies, including without
35 limitation employing one (1) or more persons registered as a lobbyist to
36 lobby on behalf of the governmental body or similar governmental bodies, if
